Animated view of Soviet Jet Fighter Aircraft, and various U.S.aircraft of the same cold war era.

Cold war era animated view of latest Soviet Jet Interceptor and Fighter Aircraft.  (Narrator mistakenly identifies the Flagon as a Su-11 but it is a Su-15.) MiG including MiG-23 planes developed by aircraft designers Mikoyan and Gurevich (MiG). Deputy Chief of Naval Operations (Air) Admiral Thomas Connolly discusses the development of United States fighter aircrafts. US aircraft F-8 Crusader landing on an Aircraft Carrier deck.  U.S. Navy F-4 Phantom fighter taking off from a Carrier deck. Aerial closeup view of formation of F-4 planes in flight. New F-14 Tomcat fighter planes described by Connolly. Location: United States. Date: 1972.
